The paper deals with generative models and disentangled representations, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of pairwise similarity labels for weak supervision suggests a focus on unsupervised or semi-supervised learning, which is often studied in the subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The datasets used in the experiments are image datasets, indicating a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of variational auto-encoders, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison with recent works that leverage adversarial training, which is a topic commonly studied in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
